Dia. 02 Bik?
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Therefore White has to cut with 1.
\par After that Black connects with 2.
\par One might think that it is bik because the liberties at the Xs are empty, but it is a big illusion.
\par
\par If Black plays at A and B, White is going to be in dansu, which means White is dead.
\par
\par }
